Actress and film producer Terry Pheto continues to fly the South African flag high on the global stage as she stars in yet another international film Pheto dazzled the red carpet at the London premiere of her latest movie ‘United Kingdom’. The actress plays Naledi Khama alongside David Oyelowo, Rosamund Pike and our very own multi award-winning actor Vusi Kunene. The film tells the love story of Sir Seretse Khama, the first president of Botswana and his wife Ruth Williams. David Oyelowo and Rosamund Pike depict the inter-racial relationship that caused an international outcry when they got married in 1948.   Pheto, who made her debut in the Academy award-winning film Tsotsi, stunned on the red carpet in a Marianne Fassler creation:     IOL